//
// test/Lower/circt/round_trip/stdin_pipe.test — M6 Phase 8 polish
// task (T139). **PASSES** post-merge: `tools/nslc/main.cpp` now
// recognises `-` as a stdin marker for every `-emit=<stage>` (not
// just `-emit=hw` — tokens / ast / mlir / hw / circt all benefit).
// The driver trampolines stdin through a `mkstemp`-created temp
// file, then passes that path to the emit function — same pipeline
// as the `-o file` case. Closes FR-026 stdin-support gap and the
// C2 finding from /speckit-analyze. The XFAIL was removed in the
// same commit that added the driver support.
//
// Test shape: pipe a known-good fixture through stdin AND through
// the file path; assert the two outputs are byte-identical.

// RUN: cat %S/zero_nsl_ops.nsl | %nslc -emit=hw - > %t.stdin.hw
// RUN: %nslc -emit=hw %S/zero_nsl_ops.nsl > %t.file.hw
// RUN: diff -q %t.stdin.hw %t.file.hw
